10
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:38,080
“Evie!” the mother cried, cradling her
daughter in a heap at her chest and running

11
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:44,140
toward the cottage. “Anna,” she said to
the little blonde, who was panting from carrying

12
00:01:44,140 --> 00:01:47,190
her friend so far, “fetch the royal physician—”

13
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:48,190
“But—”

14
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:49,190
“Go!”

15
00:01:49,190 --> 00:01:55,010
The girl didn’t protest again, fine boots
clacking against the cobblestones as she regained

16
00:01:55,010 --> 00:01:56,010
speed.

17
00:01:56,010 --> 00:02:00,860
When her mother shut the cottage door tightly
behind them, the raven-headed girl knew the

18
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:04,330
physician’s medicine wouldn’t heal her.

19
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:07,340
Only one thing would.

20
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:12,150
“Gianni!” The mother called, and the girl’s
