30
00:02:55,080 --> 00:03:00,150
They’d spent the morning together—the
blonde, the raven-haired girl, and their boy—running

31
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:06,740
through the waves, climbing rocks, dancing
in the sand. But then the afternoon came and

32
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:12,710
it was time for them to part. The boy sent
back to his castle, the little girls home—the

33
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:19,020
younger one to her mansion, ten times the
size of the other girl’s tiny cottage.

34
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:25,379
Mischievous and sunburnt, they ran in protest,
the boy leading the way, holding the girls’

35
00:03:25,379 --> 00:03:30,710
hands as they raced across the stepping-stone
rocks that led into the cove. They giggled

36
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:36,890
and shrieked as they hopped from rock to rock,
the boy’s minder chiding them from the shore.

37
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:42,710
But one rock was slick with moss. The boy
slipped—falling backward, the base of his

38
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:47,160
skull aimed directly at a crook of solid stone.

39
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:51,030
In a blink, the little girl made her choice.

40
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:55,470
She threw her body between the boy and the
jagged edge of the rock. Her back took the

41
00:03:55,470 --> 00:04:02,580
hit with a huge crack. Her head snapped back,
her skull missing impact by a hair. Just as

42
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:07,660
she hit, the boy’s head bounced onto the
pilled cotton of her bodice rather than smashing

43
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:09,540
into the rock.

44
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:12,420
It was a thing of magic that she’d made
it in time.

45
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:17,659
They were caught then. The boy’s minder
yanked them back onto the beach and told them

