47
00:04:23,260 --> 00:04:26,740
a good-bye, leaving the girls on the sand.

48
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:31,890
As they turned for home, the little raven-haired
girl stumbled, the shock wearing off and the

49
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:38,949
pain beginning. It radiated up her back, around
her rib cage, to the front of her dress. She

50
00:04:38,949 --> 00:04:44,940
couldn’t catch her breath, each inhale stopping
short. The little blonde said she’d walk

51
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:49,930
her friend home but by the time they made
it to the sea lane, the raven-headed girl

52
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:54,080
couldn’t stand, all her weight on the blonde’s
shoulders.

53
00:04:54,080 --> 00:05:01,630
“Oh, Evie . . . ,” the girl’s mother
said. As if she’d seen it all. Immediately,

54
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:07,850
she sent her husband for her bottles. Her
inks. Not that one. This one. She laid the

55
00:05:07,850 --> 00:05:11,970
girl in her bed and lit a fire with a snap
