now pin straight, her voice calm and direct.

68
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:17,259
“There is one more spell I can try.”

69
00:06:17,259 --> 00:06:22,660
With gentle fingers, she painted octopus ink
across the little girl’s cheeks, down her

70
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:28,790
neck, and across her chest. Then her mother
laid her hands gently over the girl’s chest.

71
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:31,550
“Don’t you worry, Evie.”

72
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:37,690
The words she said next were old and dark,
and the little girl didn’t understand them.

73
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:43,270
They made her blood crackle like the fire
across the room. Stole the air from the cottage.

74
00:06:43,270 --> 00:06:48,680
Made her mother shake, violently, as she held
her hands to her daughter’s skin.

75
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:55,220
The little girl couldn’t do anything but
watch her mother, her veins singing. Soon,

76
00:06:55,220 --> 00:07:00,770
her mother’s palms on her skin became more
than damp. They began to burn.

77
00:07:00,770 --> 00:07:07,130
And then the pain stopped. Air rushed into
the little girl’s lungs, and her chest rose.

78
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:11,039
She exhaled, long and deep.

79
00:07:11,039 --> 00:07:16,420
At that the girl’s mother smiled—just
before her own body began to seize, her eyes

80
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:18,680
rolling back in her head.

81
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:24,860
It was too much. The mother’s chest compressed,
a long breath pushing out—but no inhale

82
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,360
following.

83
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:32,860
“Greta! Greta!” The girl’s father placed
his hands on his wife’s face, his palms

84
00:07:32,860 --> 00:07:36,380
burning and flying away, suddenly red.

85
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:41,350
The prickle in the little girl’s blood spiked
with fear. She struggled to pull herself to

86
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:47,380
sit, her mother’s hands sliding away as
her form slumped over and her pale cheek smashed

87
00:07:47,380 --> 00:07:53,569
into the bedsheet. The little girl didn’t
hesitate, reaching for her mother’s potions.

88
00:07:53,569 --> 00:07:58,389
She turned her mother’s head to face upward
before smearing ink across those pale cheeks,

89
00:07:58,389 --> 00:08:04,139
her little fingers blistering with the touch.
Her own skin was pink and warm and full of

90
00:08:04,139 --> 00:08:09,710
life as her mother’s skin turned as white
as snow, as hot as ash.

91
00:08:09,710 --> 00:08:16,250
The girl was smart, though. She’d watched
her mother enough. She knew how these spells

92
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:22,319
worked. Magic was barter—the right words,
actions, potions for the right result.

93
00:08:22,319 --> 00:08:27,930
She put her hands on her mother’s face and
began repeating those strange words.

94
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:30,660
Words of life.

95
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:37,309
“Evelyn, no!” Her father didn’t move,
just screamed, fear freezing him to his spot

96
00:08:37,309 --> 00:08:38,739
at the foot of the bed.

97
00:08:38,739 --> 00:08:44,149
But the little girl had fumbled her way through
the words enough that her own skin began to

98
00:08:44,149 --> 00:08:51,899
grow hot. The pain returned. Her breath became
shallow. Then her mother’s eyes flew open,

99
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:55,629
showing beautiful hazel instead of the whites.

100
00:08:55,629 --> 00:08:57,769
It was working.

101
00:08:57,769 --> 00:09:04,869
Her father looked from his wife to his daughter.
Those words were dark. Old. Powerful. He knew

102
00:09:04,869 --> 00:09:08,230
this as much as he knew his native tongue.

103
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:16,110
Her mother’s lips began moving. She took
a deep breath. “Gefa!” With this single

104
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:20,980
command, she stole the words right from the
little girl’s mouth. Dark words and dark

105
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:25,160
magic and all sound gone from the girl’s
powerful tongue.

106
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:32,290
Still, the child kept going, chest heaving—she
was yelling but could not be heard. Tears

107
00:09:32,290 --> 00:09:38,179
as dark as night flowed down her little cheeks.
Black coating her vision, the girl began to

108
00:09:38,179 --> 00:09:42,009
wail without sound, her whole body shaking.

109
00:09:42,009 --> 00:09:47,720
And, with her last wisp of energy, the girl’s
mother looked to her father.

110
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:53,010
“Bring Hansa home. Tell her. Promise.”

111
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:58,420
As he nodded, her mother whispered one last
spell, and the little girl’s screams filled

112
00:09:58,420 --> 00:10:02,230
the air, black tears dripping onto her ruined
dress.

113
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:05,649
“No, Mama, no!”

114
00:10:05,649 --> 00:10:10,960
The little girl grabbed her mother’s hand,
