01:08:52,890 --> 01:08:58,430
Today, thankfully, witches are only burned
in effigy. It’s the traditional opening

826
01:08:58,430 --> 01:09:04,900
of Havnestad’s version of Lithasblot. Ours
is the earliest in the Øresund Strait, but

827
01:09:04,900 --> 01:09:11,390
we’re also the longest festival, five whole
days, drawing people from all around to watch

828
01:09:11,390 --> 01:09:18,021
the games, sing songs in celebration of Urda,
and taste plates of tvøst og spik: black

829
01:09:18,021 --> 01:09:25,350
whale meat, pink blubber, and sunny potatoes.
Even through the Tørhed, the people of Havnestad

830
01:09:25,350 --> 01:09:30,550
have always been willing to sacrifice their
limited food supply to honor the goddess.

831
01:09:30,550 --> 01:09:36,570
As the bonfire grows hot, shooting tendrils
of flames high into the salmon-toned sky,

832
01:09:36,570 --> 01:09:42,370
the festival is ready to begin. First is King
Asger’s speech of love and gamesmanship.

833
01:09:42,370 --> 01:09:46,330
Now Nik’s speech of love and gamesmanship.

834
01:09:46,330 --> 01:09:53,140
For on the night of that treacherous storm,
Nik, thankfully, still came of age. And as

835
01:09:53,140 --> 01:09:58,860
tradition demands, he must take the reins
of the festival—near-drowning is not an

836
01:09:58,860 --> 01:09:59,860
excuse.

837
01:09:59,860 --> 01:10:04,850
Thus, since regaining most of his strength,
he’s been shut away, pacing the halls of

838
01:10:04,850 --> 01:10:10,240
the palace with his father’s words on his
lips. I’ve heard him run through it twice—before

839
01:10:10,240 --> 01:10:17,540
his birthday and after, and both times he
was excellent, if not a hair too fast. Still,

840
01:10:17,540 --> 01:10:22,280
that’s just because this is new to him.
I know he’ll be amazing.

841
01:10:22,280 --> 01:10:28,370
But Crown Prince Asger Niklas Bryniulf Øldenburg
III, first in line to the throne of the sovereign

842
01:10:28,370 --> 01:10:33,470
kingdom of Havnestad, does not share my assessment.

843
01:10:33,470 --> 01:10:38,980
Nik is nearly white with nerves. His long
fingers shake as he tugs his hair flat. This

844
01:10:38,980 --> 01:10:44,210
day is already hard for the both of us—the
fourth anniversary of Anna’s drowning—and

845
01:10:44,210 --> 01:10:50,140
with the pressure of the speech added atop
that, Nik looks as if he might keel over.

846
01:10:50,140 --> 01:10:55,640
I don’t hesitate to snag a hand and press
my fingers around his. Somehow, seeing him

847
01:10:55,640 --> 01:11:01,560
so nervous calms my own reservations—about
my innovation’s trial run with Father, about

848
01:11:01,560 --> 01:11:06,910
the fact Iker has yet to arrive. I squeeze
