871
01:12:40,920 --> 01:12:46,260
Nik sighs, and I know he’s beating himself
up for such a quip—and again I’m thankful

872
01:12:46,260 --> 01:12:52,000
he knows nothing of the kisses Iker and I
shared. He squeezes me close again, the nervous

873
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:57,160
tremble subdued. “He’ll be here. Iker
makes his own rules, but he never breaks his

874
01:12:57,160 --> 01:12:58,160
word.”

875
01:12:58,160 --> 01:13:02,710
That was the last thing he said to me before
Queen Charlotte pulled him away for his final

876
01:13:02,710 --> 01:13:09,340
speech preparations. I sink to the sand and
sit, a little doll in my lap dressed in black

877
01:13:09,340 --> 01:13:15,080
and white. Ready for the ashes. I can barely
