883
01:13:39,300 --> 01:13:44,620
we burn our little witch dolls and leave this
place for good. But then I’d leave Nik for

884
01:13:44,620 --> 01:13:47,790
good too. And implicate my entire family.

885
01:13:47,790 --> 01:13:54,830
So, I sit alone—the secret witch, the prince’s
friend who doesn’t know her place.

886
01:13:54,830 --> 01:13:59,500
I am well within eyeshot of Nik as he readies
to speak—in the event that his courage has

887
01:13:59,500 --> 01:14:04,500
retreated up Lille Bjerg Pass—but far enough
to the side that I have a clear view of the

888
01:14:04,500 --> 01:14:07,160
sea in my periphery.

889
01:14:07,160 --> 01:14:08,620
He will come.

890
01:14:08,620 --> 01:14:09,980
He said he would.

891
01:14:09,980 --> 01:14:12,440
You shouldn’t care anyway.

892
01:14:12,440 --> 01:14:17,440
I turn my attention back to the royal family.
And to the flames I must face before Nik’s

893
01:14:17,440 --> 01:14:18,440
big moment.

894
01:14:18,440 --> 01:14:23,020
There’s a traditional speech honoring this
“celebration” too. And though the king

895
01:14:23,020 --> 01:14:28,060
may have ceded his duties to Nik, Queen Charlotte
