902
01:14:55,750 --> 01:15:00,290
As if the death of every Dane in the past
six hundred years was the fault of a witch.

903
01:15:00,290 --> 01:15:05,230
As if the Øldenburgs hadn’t burned hundreds
of women with flimsy proof.

904
01:15:05,230 --> 01:15:10,851
As if “the witch hunter king,” King Christian
IV, hadn’t been proud of the name he earned

905
01:15:10,851 --> 01:15:13,990
and of the lives he ruined.

906
01:15:13,990 --> 01:15:20,210
“Good evening, dear ones.” Queen Charlotte
smiles to the crowd, and it’s like ice cracking

907
01:15:20,210 --> 01:15:27,310
under pressure. “On this night, we not only
celebrate the beginning of Havnestad’s Lithasblot,

908
01:15:27,310 --> 01:15:32,220
but we remember the hardships endured by our
ancestors.”

909
01:15:32,220 --> 01:15:36,960
In the shadows, my knuckles turn white as
I clench the doll in my lap. This part is

910
01:15:36,960 --> 01:15:40,550
almost worse than tossing a replica of myself
