1042
01:27:02,240 --> 01:27:06,800
That girl—thinks herself more than a passing
fancy for the playboy prince.

1043
01:27:06,800 --> 01:27:12,370
I meet the first rocks of the cove and stand
there, letting the salt air toss my curls

1044
01:27:12,370 --> 01:27:18,210
about my face. The wind here always seems
so cleansing—like it sweeps away grime both

1045
01:27:18,210 --> 01:27:23,390
physical and mental with one exhale from the
Øresund Strait.

1046
01:27:23,390 --> 01:27:29,530
Tonight the cove is calm. The waves lap gently
about the shore, kissing both the sand and

1047
01:27:29,530 --> 01:27:34,420
the rock formations with the same delicate
precision. There is no one else in sight,

1048
01:27:34,420 --> 01:27:39,860
and this dress isn’t anything special—nothing
I have is special—so I yank off my boots

1049
01:27:39,860 --> 01:27:44,040
and stockings and place them carefully on
