1051
01:27:50,710 --> 01:27:53,940
from stone to stone until I make it to Picnic
Rock.

1052
01:27:53,940 --> 01:28:00,690
Though it’s damp from the recent high tide,
the slab isn’t so wet it’s uncomfortable.

1053
01:28:00,690 --> 01:28:06,390
I gather my skirts, pull my knees to my chest,
and sit there with my eyes closed, letting

1054
01:28:06,390 --> 01:28:09,750
the sea’s charge wash over me.

1055
01:28:09,750 --> 01:28:16,720
Finally, my heartbeat slows, and I can feel
exhaustion creeping in. But I can’t sleep

1056
01:28:16,720 --> 01:28:23,010
here. I force myself to stand on stiff legs
and grab my things. There’s barely a breeze,

1057
01:28:23,010 --> 01:28:28,850
but a tingle runs up my spine. I cross my
arms over my chest, but I can’t get rid

1058
01:28:28,850 --> 01:28:34,641
of the cold. I squint into the night, at the
shadow where the sea meets the rock formation

1059
01:28:34,641 --> 01:28:39,200
splitting the cove, when I swear I see a flash
of white skin.

1060
01:28:39,200 --> 01:28:43,000
“Hello?” I call, my body shivering.

1061
01:28:43,000 --> 01:28:48,730
