1075
01:29:38,480 --> 01:29:44,650
The boy heard the splashes, one right after
another, and stood, piccolo forgotten, eyes

1076
01:29:44,650 --> 01:29:51,000
only on the sea. He held his breath, waiting
for the first one to surface. They were both

1077
01:29:51,000 --> 01:29:55,960
strong swimmers, but the raven-curled girl
made a habit of winning.

1078
01:29:55,960 --> 01:30:01,660
It was a hundred yards to the sandbar. A worthy
swim on any day, but as the boy surveyed the

1079
01:30:01,660 --> 01:30:08,480
sea again, he knew this was not just any sea.
These were not just any waves.

1080
01:30:08,480 --> 01:30:10,730
The sea was angry.

1081
01:30:10,730 --> 01:30:15,900
The boy held his breath and took a step toward
the water, careful not to get too close—his

1082
01:30:15,900 --> 01:30:21,070
mother had often lectured him on the damage
salt water could do to his fine leather boots.

1083
01:30:21,070 --> 01:30:25,950
The blond girl surfaced first. She pulled
in a deep breath and then went back under,

1084
01:30:25,950 --> 01:30:30,880
the sandbar in her sights, still seventy-five
yards away.

1085
01:30:30,880 --> 01:30:36,320
The boy scanned the water for dark hair. Took
a breath. Squinted right at the spot where

1086
01:30:36,320 --> 01:30:40,250
she should’ve surfaced. Still nothing.

1087
01:30:40,250 --> 01:30:45,110
The blonde bobbed up again. Now ten yards
