1091
01:31:02,080 --> 01:31:07,340
back on the sea. Heart pounding. The wet boot
already coming off.

1092
01:31:07,340 --> 01:31:14,460
There. In the distance, thirty yards out.
Not the crown of a raven-haired head.

1093
01:31:14,460 --> 01:31:18,490
A single hand, reaching for air.

1094
01:31:18,490 --> 01:31:24,051
The boy dove in, full breath cinched in his
lungs, and opened his eyes. Nothing but the

1095
01:31:24,051 --> 01:31:27,340
murky deep and the sting of salt.

1096
01:31:27,340 --> 01:31:32,480
Thinking of the girls, of the hand, he surfaced
early. He would keep his stroke above the

1097
01:31:32,480 --> 01:31:37,820
waves, his head close to the surface. He was
a strong swimmer, and his new height had not

1098
01:31:37,820 --> 01:31:42,920
diminished his natural strength, but the undertow
was fiercer than he’d ever felt, constantly

1099
01:31:42,920 --> 01:31:48,280
tugging at his pant legs. A force from the
deep pulling him toward the harem of mermaids

1100
01:31:48,280 --> 01:31:53,000
all Havnestad children were told lived at
the bottom of the sea.

1101
01:31:53,000 --> 01:31:59,630
At the surface, he saw nothing. Not a strand
of hair, nor a flash of hand. But he knew

1102
01:31:59,630 --> 01:32:03,360
where they were. He knew where he must go.

1103
01:32:03,360 --> 01:32:08,260
Twenty more yards and he opened his eyes to
the sea again. Looked down. Where the undertow

1104
01:32:08,260 --> 01:32:10,200
had pulled him.

1105
01:32:10,200 --> 01:32:15,990
Black hair curled up like a cloud of ink,
pale fingers stretched toward him. Her face

1106
01:32:15,990 --> 01:32:20,920
hidden. He dove, hoping it wasn’t too late.

1107
01:32:20,920 --> 01:32:26,630
Lungs burning for air, he surfaced, one arm
hooked under her shoulders. The force of the

1108
01:32:26,630 --> 01:32:31,590
swim had pushed the curls from her face. Her
features bordered on blue, and he couldn’t

1109
01:32:31,590 --> 01:32:33,330
tell if she was breathing.

1110
01:32:33,330 --> 01:32:35,490
All he knew was that he had her.

1111
01:32:35,490 --> 01:32:41,590
“Come on, Evie. Come on.” He prayed to
the old gods as well as the Lutheran one when

1112
01:32:41,590 --> 01:32:47,340
he had the breath, his body fighting the tow
