Urda’s festival combine to create the kind

1140
01:34:35,890 --> 01:34:41,880
of charge one usually witnesses with a coming
storm. It has me up early, feeling light and

1141
01:34:41,880 --> 01:34:44,710
free after such a black night.

1142
01:34:44,710 --> 01:34:50,640
As I walk down to the harbor, amethyst in
my pocket, I see Nik’s carriage pass by.

1143
01:34:50,640 --> 01:34:55,640
I wave my hand, but I can’t tell if he’s
seen me. He’s surely headed into the valley

1144
01:34:55,640 --> 01:35:01,690
to visit the farmers in his father’s stead,
a Lithasblot tradition. We give thanks to

1145
01:35:01,690 --> 01:35:04,410
Urda but also to those who work our fields.

