hull upon capture?

1171
01:37:21,930 --> 01:37:23,730
Am I at fault?

1172
01:37:23,730 --> 01:37:31,660
I know I’m being ridiculous, but worst of
all, we would never know. All of us are here,

1173
01:37:31,660 --> 01:37:36,210
for once our eyes inward instead of turned
to the sea.

1174
01:37:36,210 --> 01:37:41,090
That sends my mind into a downward spiral
about Father, and then suddenly a shadow falls

1175
01:37:41,090 --> 01:37:46,190
across the backs of my eyelids, the direct
sun blotted out by a passing cloud. It’s

1176
01:37:46,190 --> 01:37:48,220
as if the weather worries too—

1177
01:37:48,220 --> 01:37:51,170
“Excuse me, miss?”

1178
01:37:51,170 --> 01:37:53,140
That voice.

1179
01:37:53,140 --> 01:37:59,000
My eyes pop open, searching for the face of
a friend who I know in my heart is long gone.

1180
01:37:59,000 --> 01:38:04,030
But there, leaning over me, is the girl.

1181
01:38:04,030 --> 01:38:06,780
