1484
02:03:19,280 --> 02:03:24,860
I realize she’s not here for me or my magic.
She’s here for Nik.

1485
02:03:24,860 --> 02:03:30,851
In my stunned silence, Annemette goes on.
“Is he all right? He was breathing when

1486
02:03:30,851 --> 02:03:37,300
I brought him ashore, but I didn’t have
time to—you came and then that man, and

1487
02:03:37,300 --> 02:03:43,540
I had to go. I need him to be alive, Evie.
Please, say something!”

1488
02:03:43,540 --> 02:03:52,050
I nod. “He’s fine. You saved him.” My
throat tightens and tears sting my cheeks.

1489
02:03:52,050 --> 02:03:58,330
If it wasn’t for Annemette, I’d be dressed
in mourning clothes. “He’s totally healthy.

1490
02:03:58,330 --> 02:04:02,340
Strapping. Probably milking a goat at this
very moment!”

1491
02:04:02,340 --> 02:04:08,610
Annemette practically collapses in my arms.
“Oh, thank goodness! When he fell into the

1492
02:04:08,610 --> 02:04:12,830
sea, I caught him, but the tide and the storm
