1504
02:05:11,190 --> 02:05:17,350
“Nik. His name is Nik. And he’s my best
friend. I’m so glad that you were there.

1505
02:05:17,350 --> 02:05:23,320
I saw the wave too late, and he was gone.”
I realize for the first time that after saving

1506
02:05:23,320 --> 02:05:28,400
Nik over and over again, even if it was only
on the dance floor, there was nothing I could

1507
02:05:28,400 --> 02:05:34,760
have done that night. That he’d have saved
me from the sea, but I would have failed him.

1508
02:05:34,760 --> 02:05:39,760
My smile falters and I look down to the gray
oysters at our feet. “I wish I could repay

1509
02:05:39,760 --> 02:05:43,470
you with more than a few scraps of food and
a pearl necklace.”

1510
02:05:43,470 --> 02:05:50,050
Annemette loops a finger in mine. It feels
strange, too close, but I don’t want to

1511
02:05:50,050 --> 02:05:57,020
push her away. “I didn’t do anything special,”
